<br>
<br>
how to use the 52+ on naggy/vox other than buffing ?<br>
its hard , mob hate list is limited , but a lvl 52+ will get fast hate than a lvl 52 ,, on one of naggy raids a lvl 57 necro landed 5 dots before he got banshed<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 1:08:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3424.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Small Group Tactics for Raiding Vox/Nagafen</span><hr size=1> Another tactic I have read about is to group some of the melees with a CotH mage, CotH the melee (which wipes him from the hate list as long as the mage is far enough away), have a cleric heal him (which won't banish the cleric since the melee is now not on the hate list), and send him back into the fight.<br>
<br>
I don't know how useful that would really be, since you're probably taking the melee out of the fight for at least 20 seconds or so, but I suppose if the melee gets any damage in after the heal it's better than if he had died.<br>
<br>
I had this available to me for a Vox raid I was leading and decided not to use it, mostly because on an open Vox raid you have a hard enough time getting people to follow the basics without adding any fancy stuff that requires everyone to know what they're doing.  I thought about it and then envisioned all of the CotHed people running into the bear pit...<br>
<br>
We took her down so I was happy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You should probably be careful using any tactics like this, I have to imagine VI would consider any assistance from 53+ in the actual battle an exploit.<br>
<br>
Aalek<br>
